(x-1)X'(x) + \lambda X(x) = 0
 [(x-1)^{\lambda} X(x)]' = 0 \implies X(x) = X_0 (x-1)^{-\lambda}
U(x,t) = X(x)T(t) = X_0 T_0 (x-1)^{-\lambda} e^{-(\lambda - 1) t} = K (x-1)^{-\lambda} e^{-(\lambda - 1) t^2/2}
